cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it focuses on the role of IT-facilitated interventions in encouraging friendship formation on online social networks. It could also belong to cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it studies social phenomena using computational methods. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it examines the impact of displaying information on user behavior. The paper also touches on issues related to cybersecurity and privacy, which could place it under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
